Already Installed: Python latest version
One Time: pip3 install pipenv
1) Create a directory: mkdir x
2) Navigate(cd) in the directory x
3) First Time: pipenv install django
4) To open project in VS code: code .
5) Start the Virtual environment: pipenv shell
6) Create the project in the current folder: django-admin startproject project_name .
7) python manage.py runserver optional-port_number(9000)
8) Configure terminal in VScode:
i) Open Command Palette from View menu
ii) Search: Python interpreter
iii) To get the path of the interpreter that we want, in the terminal enter and copy it: pipenv --venv
iv) In VScode select: Enter path and paste the above adding: C\...\bin\python
For example,
C:\Users\Your Name\xyz> "C:/Users/Your Name/.virtualenvs/xyz-_JAVqLtm/Scripts/activate.bat"
Manually paste the above command after updating, to enter the VE if it didn't start implicitly when you start your Terminal.
(xyz) C:\Users\Your Name\xyz> pipenv shell